data.name: Label4.Text
data.value: The "Incident Reports and Notification System" is designed to streamline the reporting of incidents and enhance communication within the school community. Its primary purpose is to enable professors and students to quickly submit incident reports, ensuring that critical information reaches administrators without delay. Once a report is received, the system automatically alerts the relevant admin staff, who can promptly call the emergency hotline for an immediate response. Additionally, the system notifies all students in the vicinity of the incident, keeping them informed and safe. This efficient process not only accelerates response times but also fosters a proactive approach to campus safety, ultimately creating a more secure learning environment for everyone.
